      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 60: `stripValidConstructs` always trims leading and trailing whitespace/newlines after stripping markdown. This changes message content in previews, replies, notification text, accessibility labels, and the iOS 14.5 bubble fallback. For example, a fenced code block containing leading/trailing blank lines or a deliberately spaced message will be displayed differently from what was sent. Avoid trimming the whole rendered body; only remove markdown syntax. \n```suggestion\nreturn text\n```",
