      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 231: Markdown link syntax is treated as renderable regardless of the destination scheme. For a message like `[tap](javascript:alert(1))`, `containsRenderableMarkdown` returns true and plain-text surfaces display only `tap`, while the bubble renderer later strips the unsafe link. That makes the visible text differ from the stored/sent content and can hide a suspicious URL. Only consider markdown links renderable when their URL passes the same http/https allowlist used by `filterDisallowedLinks`, otherwise leave the original text unchanged. Suggested direction:\n```suggestion\nstatic func containsRenderableMarkdown(in text: String) -\u003e Bool {\n    guard text.contains(where: { markerCharacters.contains($0) }) ||\n            containsMatch(for: #\"(?m)\\#(orderedListLinePattern)\"#, in: text)\n    else { return false }\n    if markdownLinkRanges(in: text).contains(where: { isAllowedMarkdownLink(in: text, range: $0) }) {\n        return true\n    }\n    return renderablePatterns.contains { containsMatch(for: $0, in: text) }\n}\n```\nwhere `isAllowedMarkdownLink` extracts the URL portion and validates it with `normalizedBubbleLinkURL`.",
